{
  "text": "Bearing this in mind, educational AI should be designed to support students' cognitive skills that are necessary for processes of higher-order thinking; for instance, GenAI could follow Bloom's taxonomy model, and nudge and guide students to stimulate critical thinking, develop higher-level thinking questions (Zhu, 2015), analyze patterns in students' responses, assess higher-order inquiry skills, and challenge students to think more deeply and critically by giving personalized feedback (Ketelhut et al., 2010)."
}